â©//Cart.js

ðŸ”´ Calculate the total price of all cart items
const total = cartItems.reduce((accumulator, item) => {
  return accumulator + item.total;
}, 0);


ðŸŒŸ cartItems is an array that contains all the items in the cart. Each item is an object with properties like title, quantity, packet, and total.

ðŸŒŸ reduce is a powerful array method in JavaScript that helps us calculate a single value based on the elements of an array. In our case, we want to calculate the total price of all cart items.

ðŸŒŸ The reduce method takes a function as its argument, which will be called for each element in the cartItems array.

ðŸŒŸ The function inside reduce takes two parameters: accumulator and item. The accumulator is like a bucket where we store the intermediate result of the calculation, and item represents each cart item in the array.

ðŸŒŸ The function returns the updated value of the accumulator plus the total value of the current item. It does this for each item in the cartItems array, accumulating the total price.

ðŸŒŸ We start the reduction with an initial value of 0 for the accumulator. This means that the first time the function is called, accumulator is 0.

ðŸŒŸ The reduce method then goes through each item in the cartItems array, adding the total value of each item to the accumulator.

ðŸŒŸ After iterating through all the items in the cartItems array, the reduce method returns the final value of the accumulator, which is the total price of all cart items.

ðŸŒŸ We store this final total price in the variable total, which we will use to display the total price of the cart items in the UI.